This paper is primarily focused on the hardware implementation of successive cancellation decoding for polar codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses techniques for optimizing the decoding process, which could fall under the categories of computer architecture (cs.AR) and embedded systems (cs.ET). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of logarithmic domain processing to reduce complexity, which could be relevant to digital signal processing (cs.DS) and control systems (cs.SY).
